                <head>42. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 13, 1961, <gloss target="#t_SIOP1">SIOP</gloss>-62 was briefed to
                    President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName>. (Enclosure to <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 2056/281, September 13; National Archives and
                    Records Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 218, <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Records, CCS 3105 Joint Planning (13 September
                    1961)) A partially declassified text is printed in International Security,
                    Summer 1987 (12:1), pages 41-51. For information on the origins of <gloss
                        target="#t_SIOP1">SIOP</gloss>-62, see <ref target="frus1958-60v03#d1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1958–1960, volume III, Documents
                        1ff</ref>.</p>
            </div>
